<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,734,1805]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,320,734,760]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Distribution:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[320,545,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[320,545,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Callitriche cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Iberian Peninsula, where it is more frequent in the south (
<bibRefCitation author="CSIC &amp; Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref14011" refString="CSIC (Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas) (2009) Anthos. Sistema de informacion sobre las plantas de Espana. (Real Jardin Botanico) and Fundacion Biodiversidad (Ministerio de Medio Ambiente), Madrid. Available at: http: // www. anthos. es (accessed December 2019)." type="url" year="2009">CSIC 2009</bibRefCitation>
), in 
<collectingCountry box="[242,326,770,796]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schotsman, H. D." box="[341,532,770,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="317 - 329" refId="ref16910" refString="Schotsman, H. D. (1965) Note sur Callitriche cribrosa nov. sp. Bulletin du Centre d'Etudes et de Recherches Scientifiques Biarritz 5 (3): 317 - 329." type="journal article" year="1965">Schotsman 1965</bibRefCitation>
), and in 
<collectingCountry box="[628,732,771,797]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, it has also been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1083,1134,770,796]" name="Italy" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Conti, F. &amp; Abbate, G. &amp; Alessandrini, A. &amp; Blasi, C." box="[1149,1342,770,797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref13907" refString="Conti, F., Abbate, G., Alessandrini, A. &amp; Blasi, C. (2005) An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Ministero dell'Ambiente e della Tutela del Territorio, Roma (Rome), 420 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Conti 
<emphasis box="[1220,1276,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Prancl, J. &amp; Fehrer, J. &amp; Caklova, P. &amp; Bambasova, V. &amp; Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z." pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="1016 - 1041" refId="ref16234" refString="Prancl, J., Fehrer, J., Caklova, P., Bambasova, V., Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z. (2020) Intricate evolutionary history of Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) taxa elucidated by a combination of DNA sequencing and genome size. Taxon 69 (5): 1016 - 1041. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12315" type="journal article" year="2020">
Prančl 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[282,386,807,833]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[397,524,806,833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[397,524,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is frequent from the coast to the Central Plateau and the Middle Atlas, from Rabat north-east to Fez and south to Ouarzazate, with isolated records from near Marrakesh and Tangiers (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1344,842,868]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,712,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-280@3.[151,1435,710,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Known distribution of Callitriche spp. in Morocco. A. C. brutia subsp. brutia, with insert map showing the position of Morocco in northwestern Africa. B. C. brutia subsp. naftolskyi. C. C. cribrosa. D. C. lusitanica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875717/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,734,1805]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,447,878,904]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[475,702,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[475,702,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Callitriche cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically grows in flowing waters of ditches, streams and river backwaters. It will tolerate nutrient enrichment, but at Oued Tizguite it appeared to have been eradicated from the main channel by excessive trampling by stock, persisting only in the spring, which was protected from stock access by a small wall. In 
<collectingCountry box="[354,458,987,1013]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[470,597,986,1013]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[470,597,986,1013]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded mainly with species typical of permanent waters such as 
<taxonomicName authority="von Linne (1753: 970)" authorityName="von Linne" authorityPageNumber="970" authorityYear="1753" box="[136,552,1022,1049]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Lemna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gibba">
<emphasis box="[136,285,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Lemna gibba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="von Linne, C." box="[293,552,1022,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref17941" refString="von Linne, C. (1753) Species Plantarum. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, 1200 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 669" type="book" year="1753">von Linné (1753: 970)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown (1812: 110)" authorityName="Brown" authorityPageNumber="110" authorityYear="1812" box="[565,1032,1022,1049]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Nasturtium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinale">
<emphasis box="[565,806,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Nasturtium officinale</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, R." box="[814,1032,1022,1049]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref13838" refString="Brown, R. (1812) Hortus Kewensis 4. Longman, Hurst, Rees, Orme &amp; Brown, London, 522 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 105339" type="book" year="1812">Brown (1812: 110)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Syme 1863: 20) Webster (1988: 20)" authorityName="Webster" authorityPageNumber="20" authorityYear="1988" baseAuthorityName="Syme" baseAuthorityPageNumber="20" baseAuthorityYear="1863" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="penicillatus" subSpecies="pseudofluitans">
<emphasis box="[1046,1317,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Ranunculus penicillatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dumortier, B. - C." pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="207 - 219" refId="ref14322" refString="Dumortier, B. - C. (1863) Monographie du genre Batrachium. Bulletin de la Societe Royale de Botanique de Belgique 2: 207 - 219. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 22308  page / 233 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1863">Dumortier 1863: 216</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Babington, C. C." box="[269,501,1058,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref13273" refString="Babington, C. C. (1874) Manual of British botany, containing the flowering plants and ferns. Arranged according to the natural orders, 7 th ed. J. Van Voorst, London, 473 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 132532" type="book" year="1874">Babington (1874: 7)</bibRefCitation>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[589,752,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">pseudofluitans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Syme, J. T. B." box="[769,946,1058,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref17486" refString="Syme, J. T. B. (1863) English Botany; or, Coloured figures of British plants, ed. 3 [B], 1. R. Hardwicke, London, 235 pp." type="book" year="1863">Syme 1863: 20</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Webster, S. D." box="[962,1184,1058,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref18186" refString="Webster, S. D. (1988) Ranunculus penicillatus (Dumort.) Bab. in Great Britain and Ireland. Watsonia 17: 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1988">Webster (1988: 20)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pennell (1921: 37)" authorityName="Pennell" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1921" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Veronica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis box="[1247,1451,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Veronica catenata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pennell, F. W." box="[136,348,1094,1120]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="29 - 41" refId="ref16011" refString="Pennell, F. W. (1921) &quot; Veronica &quot; in North and South America. Rhodora 23 (266): 29 - 41." type="journal article" year="1921">Pennell (1921: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In the spring at Oued Tizguite it also occurred with a rhodophyte [
<taxonomicName class="Florideophyceae" family="Batrachospermaceae" genus="Batrachospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1103,1310,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Batrachospermum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roth, A. W." pageId="5" pageNumber="58" refId="ref16581" refString="Roth, A. W. (1797) Bemerkungen uber das Studium der cryptogamischen Wassergewachse. Gebrudern Hahn, Hannover, 109 pp. [https: // archive. org / details / bemerkungenberd 00 rothgoog]" type="book" year="1797">Roth (1797: 37)</bibRefCitation>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
], which typically occurs in cold waters (N. Willby, pers. comm. 2005).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,734,1805]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1166,1192]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[370,592,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis box="[370,592,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Callitriche cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[961,1170,1166,1192]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[961,1082,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1343,1447,1167,1193]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[218,353,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis box="[218,353,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the combination of the large, broadly winged fruit that are greyish-brown when mature, and large anthers with yellow pollen. It can often be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[886,1018,1238,1265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis box="[886,1018,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the broad floating leaves with more than seven parallel veins, however when this character is lacking it can only reliably be distinguished by the cribrose testa of the fruit.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,734,1805]" box="[189,902,1346,1372]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
